<h4>The adapter contract</h4>
<p><code>\local_unifiedgrader\adapter\base_adapter</code> is abstract and
defines (among others):</p>

<ul>
    <li><code>get_activity_info(): array</code> — name, type, due dates, max grade, grading method, feature flags.</li>
    <li><code>get_participants(array $filters): array</code> — filtered list with status, submission time, grade, late flag, override flag.</li>
    <li><code>get_submission_data(int $userid): array</code> — content / files / portfolio URL / hascontent flag / attempts.</li>
    <li><code>get_grade_data(int $userid): array</code> — current grade, feedback, rubric fill data.</li>
    <li><code>save_grade(...)</code> — write grade, feedback, advanced grading data.</li>
    <li><code>get_submission_files(int $userid): array</code> — files for the right-rail file selector.</li>
    <li><code>supports_feature(string $feature): bool</code> — feature gates: rubric, markingguide, onlinetext, filesubmission, blindmarking, annotations, plagiarism.</li>
    <li><code>is_grade_released(int $userid): bool</code> — whether students should see their grade.</li>
</ul>

<p>Optional methods cover attempts, plagiarism links, rubric/marking
guide integration, draft-area handling, submission-action handlers, and
override / extension management.</p>

