<h3>Hooks &amp; navigation</h3>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Settings navigation</strong>: <code>local_unifiedgrader_extend_settings_navigation()</code> in <code>lib.php</code> adds a <em>Grading interface</em> tab to <code>modulesettings</code> for supported activity types.</li>
    <li><strong>PSR-14 hook</strong> <code>before_standard_top_of_body_html_generation</code> (registered in <code>db/hooks.php</code>, callback in <code>classes/hook_callbacks.php</code>): redirects native <em>Grade</em> buttons to the unified grader for teachers, and injects feedback banners + chat-bubble widgets for students.</li>
    <li><strong>Pluginfile callback</strong> <code>local_unifiedgrader_pluginfile()</code> serves files for the plugin's fileareas (<code>annotatedpdf</code>, <code>forumfeedback</code>, <code>quizfeedback</code>, <code>bbbfeedback</code>, <code>onlinetextpdf</code>) with capability checks.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Web services</h3>

<p>All declared in <code>db/services.php</code>, all marked
<code>ajax: true</code>. Capability checks happen at the service entry
point. Notable services:</p>

<ul>
    <li><code>local_unifiedgrader_get_submission_data</code> — adapter dispatches; returns <code>hascontent</code>, files, portfolio URL, attempts.</li>
    <li><code>local_unifiedgrader_save_grade</code> — central save path including penalty application.</li>
    <li><code>local_unifiedgrader_save_annotations</code> + <code>save_annotated_pdf</code> — annotation persistence.</li>
    <li><code>local_unifiedgrader_refresh_bbb_engagement</code> — triggers a server-side scrape of BBB statistics pages.</li>
    <li><code>local_unifiedgrader_clear_all_overrides</code> — single action to clear overrides + extensions for a user.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Building &amp; testing</h3>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Build</strong>: <code>./deploy.sh</code> from the dev folder rsyncs to Moodle, runs <code>npx grunt amd</code>, copies built files back. Run after editing any AMD module.</li>
    <li><strong>Tests</strong>: <code>vendor/bin/phpunit --testsuite local_unifiedgrader_testsuite</code> from Moodle root (PHP 8.3 via MAMP). 380+ tests, 1000+ assertions.</li>
    <li><strong>Linting</strong>: ESLint runs as part of <code>grunt amd</code>. Mustache lint via Moodle's <code>moodle-cs</code>.</li>
</ul>
</section>
